2 Section 9. Section 61-8-607, MCA, is amended to read:
3 "61-8-607. Lamps and other equipment on bicycles, and mopeds, or motorized scooters. (1) A
4 bicycle, or moped, or motorized scooter when in use at dawn, dusk, or nighttime must be equipped with:
5 (a) a lamp on the front emitting a white light visible from a distance of at least 500 feet to the front.
6 In lieu of a lamp affixed to the bicycle, or moped, or motorized scooter, a bicyclist rider may use a lamp with
7 equal intensity and visibility affixed to the cyclist's rider's helmet and facing forward.
8 (b) facing the rear, either a lamp emitting a red light visible from a distance of at least 500 feet to
9 the rear or a red reflector visible from a distance of at least 500 feet to the rear when illuminated by low-beam
10 motor vehicle headlamps. In lieu of a lamp affixed to the bicycle, moped, or motorized scooter, a rider may use
11 a red lamp with equal intensity and visibility affixed to the rider and facing the rear.; and
12 (c) reflective material large and reflective enough to be visible from the left and right sides from a
13 distance of at least 500 feet when illuminated by low-beam motor vehicle headlamps.
14 (2) A bicycle, or moped, or motorized scooter must be equipped with a brake enabling the operator
15 to stop the bicycle or, moped, or motorized scooter within no more than 25 feet from a speed of 10 miles an
16 hour on dry, level, clean pavement."
