8 Section 11. Section 61-8-609, MCA, is amended to read:
9 "61-8-609. Bicycle, or moped, or motorized scooter racing -- when lawful. (1) Bicycle, or moped,
10 or motorized scooter racing on a highway is prohibited except as authorized in this section.
11 (2) Bicycle or, moped, or motorized scooter racing on a highway is lawful when a racing event is
12 approved by state or local authorities on any highway under their respective jurisdictions. Approval of bicycle or
13 moped highway racing events may be granted only under conditions that ensure reasonable safety for all race
14 participants, spectators, and other highway users and that prevent unreasonable interference with traffic flow.
15 (3) By agreement with the approving authority, participants in an approved bicycle, or moped, or
16 motorized scooter highway racing event may be exempted from compliance with any traffic laws otherwise
17 applicable if traffic control is adequate to ensure the safety of all highway users."
18
19 Section 12. Section 61-9-417, MCA, is amended to read:
20 "61-9-417. Headgear required for minor motorcycle riders. (1) (a) Except as provided in
21 subsection (1)(b), an operator and passenger under 18 years of age of a motorcycle, moped, motorized
22 scooter, or quadricycle operated on the streets or highways of this state shall wear protective headgear on the
23 head. The headgear must meet standards established by the department of justice.
24 (b) This section does not apply to an operator and passenger of an autocycle as defined in 61-1-
25 101 that is completely enclosed with a windshield, nonremovable doors, and a roof.
26 (2) A person may not operate a motorcycle, moped, motorized scooter, or quadricycle upon a
27 highway in the state unless all passengers under 18 years of age are in compliance with subsection (1)."
